# CODEOWNERS — moderation chokepoint for the public plugin registry.
#
# Every submission (catalog/**) and publisher registration (publishers/**)
# requires a review from the AiHummer maintainers before it can merge. This is
# the "AI-assist + MANDATORY HUMAN" policy: the AI reviewer (ai-review.yml) posts
# a verdict, but a human maintainer ALWAYS makes the final merge decision.
#
# NOTE: external plugin authors do NOT have write access to this repo, so they
# cannot self-merge their own PRs regardless of CODEOWNERS — branch protection +
# the maintainers' exclusive merge right is the real chokepoint. CODEOWNERS makes
# the required-review explicit and routes the request to the right team.
#
# To enforce this, enable branch protection on `main`:
#   - Require a pull request before merging
#   - Require review from Code Owners
#   - (recommended) Require the `validate` status check to pass

# Submissions and publisher identities — maintainer review required.
/catalog/      @AiHummer/maintainers
/publishers/   @AiHummer/maintainers

# The CI, scripts, moderation policy and revoke list — maintainer review required.
/.github/      @AiHummer/maintainers
/scripts/      @AiHummer/maintainers
/revoked.json  @AiHummer/maintainers
/MODERATION.md @AiHummer/maintainers
